## useMemo for Expensive Computations

```ts
const sortedItems = useMemo(
  () => items.slice().sort((a, b) => a.name.localeCompare(b.name)),
  [items]
);
```

## Compositor Hook (Page-level)

```ts
export function useUserPage(userId: string) {
  const user = useUser(userId);
  const permissions = usePermissions();
  const { toast } = useToast();

  const handleUpdate = useCallback(async (data: UpdateUserDTO) => {
    await updateUser.mutateAsync(data);
    toast({ title: "User updated" });
  }, []);

  return { user, permissions, handleUpdate };
}
```

## Conventions

- `use` prefix is mandatory
- Typed return interface: `Use{Name}Return`
- `useCallback` for functions passed as props
- `useMemo` only for truly expensive computations
- Query keys as constant objects
- Compositor hook to orchestrate hooks in pages
- Mandatory cleanup in `useEffect` with subscriptions
